    "where ϱ ∈ [0, 1) defines the level of uncertainty.",
    "For example, ϱ = 0.04 means that the diagonal elements of the covariance matrix can change by up to 4% (so the volatilites can change by around 2%), and the asset return correlations can change by up to around 4%.",
